# Backend Standards

## Clean Architecture Layers
- `domain/` — pure Python, no framework imports
- `application/` — use cases, depends on domain + infrastructure interfaces
- `infrastructure/` — SQLAlchemy models, repos, OpenRouter client
- `api/v1/` — FastAPI routers, Pydantic request/response schemas

## Patterns
- All DB access through Repository classes (not directly in services)
- Use `AsyncSession` from SQLAlchemy for all DB operations
- Pydantic v2: use `model_config = ConfigDict(from_attributes=True)`
- Return typed responses, never raw dicts from endpoints

## SQL Guardrails (mandatory before any AI SQL execution)
```python
FORBIDDEN_KEYWORDS = ["DROP", "DELETE", "TRUNCATE", "ALTER", "UPDATE", "INSERT", "GRANT", "REVOKE"]
SENSITIVE_COLUMNS = ["password", "token", "secret", "phone", "email"]
```
Always call `SecurityService.validate_sql(sql)` before `QueryExecutor.run(sql)`.

## AI Response Handling
- OpenRouter response includes `choices[0].message.reasoning_content` for thinking
- Always extract and store `reasoning_content` in `query_logs.ai_thinking`
- Return both `sql`, `thinking`, and `result` in API response

## Error Handling
- Use custom exceptions from `domain/exceptions.py`
- Return structured `{"error": "...", "code": "..."}` — never raw tracebacks
